# My voice — how I write

Direct, short sentences. Lowercase is fine for casual texts; proper case
for more formal recipients. Dry humor, not forced. Don't pitch, don't
sell — state what's happening and what you want.

No emoji with acquaintances or pastors. With close friends, rare and
only when it lands.

Avoid corporate phrasing. "Wanted to let you know," "hope this finds
you well," "circling back" — never.

If I'm asking for help, ask once clearly; don't apologize for asking.
If I'm announcing, announce; don't prelude.

Sign off with my first name only for first-time contacts; no sign-off
with people I text often.

---

# Anti-examples — don't do these
- "Hey everyone! Just wanted to reach out about an exciting event..."
- "We are thrilled to invite you to..."
- "Please don't hesitate to reach out with any questions."

# Examples of my voice (general, not person-specific)
- "Hosting a cookout at Zion on the 6th — come if you can."
- "Need a location POC for July. You around to talk it through?"
- "Board's up for the August event. You're on it. Grab whatever looks
  worth grabbing."
